        "show_seo_content": true,
        "seo_content": "<h3>What is an upholstered bed?</h3><p>An upholstered bed is a bed frame that is fully wrapped in fabric — velvet, chenille, linen, or a durable weave — and padded throughout, giving it a soft, luxurious finish from headboard to base. Unlike traditional wooden or metal frames, an upholstered bed adds warmth, texture, and a sense of hotel-style refinement to any bedroom. The padded headboard also doubles as a comfortable backrest for reading or watching TV.</p><h3>What fabrics and colours are available?</h3><p>Our upholstered beds are available in a curated range of premium fabrics including plush velvet, rich chenille, and hard-wearing textured weave. Each fabric comes in multiple colourways — from classic creams and elegant greys to statement blacks and deep jewel tones — so you can tailor the look to your bedroom's palette. Colour swatches are available on each product listing so you can see exactly what you're getting.</p><h3>What headboard styles do you offer?</h3><p>We offer several headboard designs across our upholstered range. Wingback headboards feature angled side panels that wrap around you slightly, creating a more cocooned, enveloping feel. Panel headboards offer a clean, modern look with a flat, neatly stitched finish. Button-studded and channel-tufted designs add a touch of classic luxury, while low-profile options suit contemporary, minimal bedrooms. Each style is available in the full range of fabrics and colours.</p><h3>Do upholstered beds come with storage?</h3><p>Yes — most of our upholstered beds are available with optional built-in storage drawers. You can typically choose from two or four drawers positioned on either side of the base for easy, everyday access. Ottoman-style options are also available, where the entire base lifts up on gas-lift pistons to reveal a large under-bed storage compartment — ideal for duvets, pillows, and seasonal items.</p><h3>What sizes are available?</h3><p>Our upholstered beds are available in all standard UK sizes: Small Single (2FT6), Single (3FT), Small Double (4FT), Double (4FT6), King (5FT), and Super King (6FT). All sizes are available across our full range of fabrics and headboard styles, with storage options on most models. The size you need depends on your mattress — if you have an existing mattress, simply match the size.</p><h3>Do upholstered beds come with a mattress?</h3><p>It depends on the listing. Some of our upholstered beds are sold as a complete bundle with a Klawford mattress included — often at a saving compared to buying separately. Others are available as a frame only, giving you the freedom to pair them with a mattress you already own or choose one from our mattress range. Check the product options on each listing to see what's included.</p><h3>Are upholstered beds easy to clean and maintain?</h3><p>Most of our upholstered fabrics are designed for everyday durability. For routine care, a soft-bristle brush or upholstery attachment on a vacuum keeps the fabric looking fresh and removes dust. Spills should be blotted immediately with a clean, dry cloth — avoid rubbing. For deeper cleaning, a specialist upholstery spray or fabric shampoo works well. Velvet fabrics benefit from occasional brushing in the direction of the pile to restore their sheen.</p><h3>How do I assemble an upholstered bed?</h3><p>All our upholstered beds are delivered flat-packed and are designed for straightforward home assembly. Full step-by-step illustrated instructions are included with every order, and all necessary fixings come in the box. Most frames can be assembled in under an hour with a second pair of hands. If you have any questions during assembly, our customer service team is on hand to help.</p>"
